<LegalLayout
  title="Data Deletion Request"
  description="How to request data deletion for Frecuencia Global Publisher."
  lastUpdated="April 16, 2026"
  lang="en"
>
  <p>
    <strong>Frecuencia Global Publisher</strong> provides a formal process for requesting deletion of personal data associated with your interactions with Frecuencia Global services.
  </p>

  <h2>1. What You Can Request</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Deletion of contact information voluntarily provided to Frecuencia Global.</li>
    <li>Deletion of support or communication records linked to your request history.</li>
    <li>Removal of personal data that is no longer required for legal or operational purposes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Platform Data Clarification</h2>
  <p>
    Frecuencia Global Publisher does not control end-user account data stored directly by third-party social platforms. For platform-native data (for example TikTok account data managed by TikTok), please also use the platform's own privacy and deletion controls.
  </p>

  <h2>3. How to Submit a Deletion Request</h2>
  <p>
    Send your request to <a href="mailto:contacto@frecuenciaglobal.org">contacto@frecuenciaglobal.org</a> with the subject line: <strong>Data Deletion Request</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>Please include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your full name.</li>
    <li>Your contact email.</li>
    <li>A clear description of the data you want deleted.</li>
    <li>Context that helps us locate the record (date, channel, or interaction reference).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Processing Timeline</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Request acknowledgement:</strong> typically within 48 business hours.</li>
    <li><strong>Resolution window:</strong> typically within 7 to 14 business days, depending on complexity.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Revoking Platform Access</h2>
  <p>
    If your request involves connected social accounts, revoke Frecuencia Global Publisher permissions from the relevant platform settings (for example TikTok app permissions), and include that status in your email request.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Legal Exceptions</h2>
  <p>
    Certain records may be retained when required by law, security obligations, or legitimate compliance needs. If this applies, we will explain what cannot be deleted and why.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Contact</h2>
  <div class="contact-box">
    <p>
      <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contacto@frecuenciaglobal.org">contacto@frecuenciaglobal.org</a><br>
      <strong>Related policy:</strong> <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</LegalLayout>
